  "texts": [
    "For this reason, the graph pooling technique has emerged, which is dedicated to integrating the global attributes and local node properties of the entire graph, thus compensating for the shortcomings of traditional graph neural networks in this regard.",
    "It ensures that the overall pattern and subtle node differences of the graph can be fully reflected when performing graph-level representations, thus optimizing the performance of various tasks such as graph classification and graph regression.",
    "To improve the graph-level representation learning capability, numerous graph pooling methods have been proposed, among which the most representative ones are Diffpool (Zhang et al. 2020), Gpool (Gao and Ji 2019b), SAGPool (Lee et al. 2019), etc.",
    "According to how the coarsened graph is formed, graph pooling can be classified into early pooling, global pooling, and hierarchical pooling.",
    "Figure 2 outlines the taxonomy and representative methods of graph pooling."
  ],
